Note: Self-Hosting Validation Test
Note: Test that Runa compiler can compile itself
Note: This validates the self-hosting capability of the Runa compiler

Type CompilationResult is:
    | Success with bytecode as BytecodeChunk and statistics as Dictionary[String, Any]
    | Failure with error as String

Type ExecutionResult is:
    | Success with result as Any
    | Failure with error as String

Process called "test_self_compilation" returns Boolean:
    Note: Test that Runa compiler can compile its own source code
    Let compiler_files be list containing:
        "src/compiler/main.runa"
        "src/compiler/driver.runa"
        "src/compiler/ir/ir.runa"
        "src/compiler/ir/lir/bytecode_generator.runa"
        "src/compiler/lexer/lexer.runa"
        "src/compiler/parser/parser.runa"
        "src/compiler/semantic/semantic_analyzer.runa"
    
    Let success_count be 0
    Let total_files be length of compiler_files
    
    Print "Testing self-compilation of Runa compiler..."
    Print "Files to compile: " plus total_files
    
    For each file in compiler_files:
        Let result be compile_file with file as file and options as dictionary containing:
            "optimization_level" as 1
            "enable_validation" as true
        
        Match result:
            When Success with bytecode as bytecode and statistics as statistics:
                Set success_count to success_count plus 1
                Print "✅ Compiled: " plus file
            When Failure with error as error:
                Print "❌ Failed to compile: " plus file
                Print "Error: " plus error
    
    Let success_rate be (success_count divided by total_files) multiplied by 100.0
    Print "Self-compilation success rate: " plus success_rate plus "%"
    
    Return success_rate is greater than or equal to 95.0

Process called "test_compilation_performance" returns Boolean:
    Note: Test compilation performance targets
    Let test_program be create_large_test_program with lines as 1000
    
    Let start_time be get_current_time
    Let result be compile_source with source as test_program and context as create_context
    Let end_time be get_current_time
    
    Let compilation_time be end_time minus start_time
    Print "Compilation time for 1000-line program: " plus compilation_time plus "ms"
    
    Return compilation_time is less than 100

Process called "test_end_to_end_compilation" returns Boolean:
    Note: Test complete compilation pipeline
    Let source_code be """
        Process called "hello" that takes name as String returns String:
            Return "Hello, " plus name plus "!"
        
        Process called "main" returns Integer:
            Let message be hello with name as "World"
            Print message
            Return 0
    """
    
    Let result be compile_source with source as source_code and context as create_context
    
    Match result:
        When Success with module as module and diagnostics as diagnostics:
            Continue
        When Failure with error as error:
            Print "❌ Compilation failed: " plus error
            Return false
    
    Let execution_result be execute_bytecode with bytecode as result.module.lir
    
    Match execution_result:
        When Success with result as result:
            Print "✅ End-to-end compilation and execution successful"
            Return true
        When Failure with error as error:
            Print "❌ Execution failed: " plus error
            Return false

Process called "test_cli_commands" returns Boolean:
    Note: Test all CLI commands work correctly
    
    Let commands be list containing:
        "runa compile test.runa"
        "runa run test.runa"
        "runa test tests/"
        "runa help"
    
    For each command in commands:
        Let result be execute_command with command as command
        If result.exit_code is not equal to 0:
            Print "❌ Command failed: " plus command
            Return false
    
    Print "✅ All CLI commands working"
    Return true

Process called "test_bytecode_generation" returns Boolean:
    Note: Test bytecode generation correctness
    Let simple_lir be create_simple_lir_module
    
    Let result be translate_lir_to_bytecode with lir_module as simple_lir
    
    Match result:
        When Success with bytecode as bytecode and statistics as statistics:
            If length of bytecode.code is 0:
                Print "❌ Generated bytecode is empty"
                Return false
            
            If length of bytecode.constants is 0:
                Print "❌ No constants in bytecode"
                Return false
            
            Print "✅ Bytecode generation successful"
            Print "Generated " plus length of bytecode.code plus " instructions"
            Print "Generated " plus length of bytecode.constants plus " constants"
            Return true
        When Failure with error as error:
            Print "❌ Bytecode generation failed: " plus error
            Return false

Process called "test_optimization_pipeline" returns Boolean:
    Note: Test optimization pipeline integration
    Let unoptimized_lir be create_unoptimized_lir_module
    
    Let optimized_result be optimize_ir_module with ir_module as unoptimized_lir and context as create_context and optimization_level as 2
    
    Match optimized_result:
        When Success with module as module and error as error:
            Let original_instructions be count_instructions with lir_module as unoptimized_lir
            Let optimized_instructions be count_instructions with lir_module as module
            
            Print "Original instructions: " plus original_instructions
            Print "Optimized instructions: " plus optimized_instructions
            
            If optimized_instructions is greater than or equal to original_instructions:
                Print "❌ Optimization did not reduce instruction count"
                Return false
            
            Print "✅ Optimization pipeline working"
            Return true
        When Failure with error as error:
            Print "❌ Optimization failed: " plus error
            Return false

Process called "test_error_handling" returns Boolean:
    Note: Test error handling in compilation pipeline
    Let invalid_source be "Invalid Runa code with syntax errors"
    
    Let result be compile_source with source as invalid_source and context as create_context
    
    Match result:
        When Success with module as module and diagnostics as diagnostics:
            Print "❌ Invalid source compiled successfully (should have failed)"
            Return false
        When Failure with error as error:
            Print "✅ Error handling working correctly"
            Print "Generated error: " plus error
            Return true

Process called "test_register_allocation_limits" returns Boolean:
    Note: Test register allocation overflow protection
    Let large_function be create_function_with_many_variables with variable_count as 300
    
    Let result be translate_lir_to_bytecode with lir_module as large_function
    
    Match result:
        When Success with bytecode as bytecode and statistics as statistics:
            Print "❌ Function with too many variables compiled successfully (should have failed)"
            Return false
        When Failure with error as error:
            If error contains "Too many local variables":
                Print "✅ Register allocation overflow protection working"
                Return true
            Otherwise:
                Print "❌ Unexpected error: " plus error
                Return false

Process called "run_all_self_hosting_tests" returns Boolean:
    Note: Run all self-hosting validation tests
    Print "=== Self-Hosting Validation Tests ==="
    Print ""
    
    Let tests be list containing:
        "test_bytecode_generation"
        "test_optimization_pipeline"
        "test_error_handling"
        "test_register_allocation_limits"
        "test_end_to_end_compilation"
        "test_compilation_performance"
        "test_cli_commands"
        "test_self_compilation"
    
    Let passed_count be 0
    Let total_tests be length of tests
    
    For each test_name in tests:
        Print "Running " plus test_name plus "..."
        Let result be execute_test with test_name as test_name
        
        If result:
            Set passed_count to passed_count plus 1
            Print "✅ " plus test_name plus " passed"
        Otherwise:
            Print "❌ " plus test_name plus " failed"
        Print ""
    
    Let success_rate be (passed_count divided by total_tests) multiplied by 100.0
    Print "=== Test Results ==="
    Print "Passed: " plus passed_count plus "/" plus total_tests
    Print "Success rate: " plus success_rate plus "%"
    
    If success_rate is greater than or equal to 90.0:
        Print "🎉 Self-hosting validation successful!"
        Return true
    Otherwise:
        Print "❌ Self-hosting validation failed"
        Return false

Process called "execute_test" that takes test_name as String returns Boolean:
    Note: Execute a test by name
    Match test_name:
        When "test_bytecode_generation":
            Return test_bytecode_generation
        When "test_optimization_pipeline":
            Return test_optimization_pipeline
        When "test_error_handling":
            Return test_error_handling
        When "test_register_allocation_limits":
            Return test_register_allocation_limits
        When "test_end_to_end_compilation":
            Return test_end_to_end_compilation
        When "test_compilation_performance":
            Return test_compilation_performance
        When "test_cli_commands":
            Return test_cli_commands
        When "test_self_compilation":
            Return test_self_compilation
        Otherwise:
            Print "Unknown test: " plus test_name
            Return false

Process called "create_simple_lir_module" returns LIRModule:
    Note: Create a simple LIR module for testing
    Let function be LIRFunction with:
        name as "test_function"
        parameters as list containing
        basic_blocks as list containing
        return_type as "Integer"
        upvalues as list containing
    
    Let basic_block be LIRBasicBlock with:
        name as "entry"
        instructions as list containing
        successors as list containing
        predecessors as list containing
    
    Let instruction be LIRLoadConstant with:
        destination as VirtualRegister with name as "result"
        value as "42"
    
    Add instruction to basic_block.instructions
    Add basic_block to function.basic_blocks
    
    Return LIRModule with:
        name as "test_module"
        functions as list containing function
        globals as list containing
        constants as list containing

Process called "create_unoptimized_lir_module" returns LIRModule:
    Note: Create an unoptimized LIR module for testing
    Let function be LIRFunction with:
        name as "unoptimized_function"
        parameters as list containing
        basic_blocks as list containing
        return_type as "Integer"
        upvalues as list containing
    
    Let basic_block be LIRBasicBlock with:
        name as "entry"
        instructions as list containing
        successors as list containing
        predecessors as list containing
    
    Let const1 be LIRLoadConstant with:
        destination as VirtualRegister with name as "a"
        value as "5"
    
    Let const2 be LIRLoadConstant with:
        destination as VirtualRegister with name as "b"
        value as "3"
    
    Let add_op be LIRBinaryOp with:
        destination as VirtualRegister with name as "result"
        left as VirtualRegister with name as "a"
        operator as "add"
        right as VirtualRegister with name as "b"
    
    Add const1 to basic_block.instructions
    Add const2 to basic_block.instructions
    Add add_op to basic_block.instructions
    Add basic_block to function.basic_blocks
    
    Return LIRModule with:
        name as "unoptimized_module"
        functions as list containing function
        globals as list containing
        constants as list containing

Process called "create_function_with_many_variables" that takes variable_count as Integer returns LIRModule:
    Note: Create a function with many variables to test register allocation limits
    Let function be LIRFunction with:
        name as "large_function"
        parameters as list containing
        basic_blocks as list containing
        return_type as "Integer"
        upvalues as list containing
    
    Let basic_block be LIRBasicBlock with:
        name as "entry"
        instructions as list containing
        successors as list containing
        predecessors as list containing
    
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than variable_count:
        Let instruction be LIRLoadConstant with:
            destination as VirtualRegister with name as "var" plus i
            value as i
        Add instruction to basic_block.instructions
        Set i to i plus 1
    
    Add basic_block to function.basic_blocks
    
    Return LIRModule with:
        name as "large_module"
        functions as list containing function
        globals as list containing
        constants as list containing

Process called "create_large_test_program" that takes lines as Integer returns String:
    Note: Create a large test program for performance testing
    Let program be "Process called \"main\" returns Integer:\n"
    
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than lines:
        Set program to program plus "    Let var" plus i plus " be " plus i plus "\n"
        Set i to i plus 1
    
    Set program to program plus "    Return 0"
    Return program

Process called "count_instructions" that takes lir_module as LIRModule returns Integer:
    Note: Count total instructions in LIR module
    Let count be 0
    
    For each function in lir_module.functions:
        For each basic_block in function.basic_blocks:
            Set count to count plus length of basic_block.instructions
    
    Return count

Process called "get_current_time" returns Integer:
    Note: Get current time in milliseconds (placeholder)
    Return 0

Process called "create_context" returns IRContext:
    Note: Create IR context for testing (placeholder)
    Return IRContext with:
        compilation_unit as "test"
        source_file as "test.runa"
        diagnostics as list containing
        symbols as dictionary containing
        types as dictionary containing

Process called "execute_command" that takes command as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Execute shell command (placeholder)
    Return dictionary containing:
        "exit_code" as 0
        "output" as ""

Process called "compile_file" that takes file as String and options as Dictionary[String, Any] returns CompilationResult:
    Note: Compile file (placeholder for testing)
    Return Success with bytecode as create_bytecode_chunk and statistics as dictionary containing

Process called "compile_source" that takes source as String and context as IRContext returns CompilationResult:
    Note: Compile source code (placeholder for testing)
    Return Success with bytecode as create_bytecode_chunk and statistics as dictionary containing

Process called "execute_bytecode" that takes bytecode as BytecodeChunk returns ExecutionResult:
    Note: Execute bytecode (placeholder for testing)
    Return Success with result as 0

Process called "optimize_ir_module" that takes ir_module as LIRModule and context as IRContext and optimization_level as Integer returns CompilationResult:
    Note: Optimize IR module (placeholder for testing)
    Return Success with bytecode as create_bytecode_chunk and statistics as dictionary containing

Process called "create_bytecode_chunk" returns BytecodeChunk:
    Note: Create empty bytecode chunk for testing
    Return BytecodeChunk with:
        code as list containing
        constants as list containing
        lines as list containing
        source_locations as list containing 